@startuml SignalCaptureAI_V0_DataCapture_Workflow
title SignalCaptureAI V0 - Data Capture Workflow (EU Only)
skinparam style strictuml
skinparam wrapWidth 200

legend top right
  **Risk Levels (Transactions & Actor Swimlanes)**
  |<#White> White Box | Internal / Trusted Execution (Low Risk) |
  |<#E6F2FF> <color:black>Light Blue Lane</color> | Internal Trusted System Boundary |
  |<#Orange> Orange Box | PII Processing (Medium Risk) |
  |<#FFE6CC> <color:black>Light Orange Lane</color>| Auth / Transit (Medium Risk) |
  |<#Red> <color:white>Red Box</color> | External Data Ingress-Egress (High Risk) |
  |<#FFCCCC> <color:black>Light Red Lane</color>| Untrusted External Actors (High Risk) |
endlegend

|#FFCCCC|Sales Rep|
start
:Access SignalCaptureAI Platform\n(HTTPS / TLS 1.3);

|#FFE6CC|WorkOS (SSO)|
:Authenticate User (SSO / Magic Link);
note right
  WorkOS SSO in V0.
  HTTP-only Secure cookie session.
  Control Centre: MFA enforced.
end note

|#E6F2FF|API Gateway (Fastify) — Azure Container Apps|
:Issue Session Cookie (httpOnly, Secure,\nSameSite=Lax) with Signed Location Header (EU);
note right
  Location context via
  HMAC-SHA256 signed headers
  (location-header package).
  No external edge network in V0.
end note

|#FFCCCC|Sales Rep|
:Select Event in App;
:Capture Business Card (Camera Capture)\n& Record Voice Note (Voice Recorder); <<#Red>>

|#FFCCCC|Sales Rep (Client-Side)|
:Run Tesseract.js OCR in Browser; <<#Orange>>
note right
  OCR runs entirely client-side.
  No business card image PII
  sent to server for OCR.
  Only extracted text is uploaded.
end note
:Encode Voice Note (WebM / Opus); <<#Orange>>

|#E6F2FF|API Gateway (Fastify) — Azure Container Apps|
:Receive Submission over HTTPS / TLS 1.3\n(OCR text + audio file);
:Extract Signed Location Header → Confirm EU Context\n(HMAC-SHA256 validation, 60s expiry, nonce replay check);

|#E6F2FF|Whisper Service (OpenAI)|
:Pass Audio to OpenAI Whisper\nfor Transcription; <<#Orange>>
note right
  Voice PII transmitted to
  OpenAI external API.
  GDPR risk — DPA required.
  V1: migrate to Azure AI Speech.
end note
:Return Transcript (PII stripped); <<#Orange>>

|#E6F2FF|API Gateway (Fastify) — Azure Container Apps|
:SET LOCAL app.current_tenant_id\n(RLS + Citus sharding isolation);
:Fetch Firm Context from CosmosDB PostgreSQL;

|#E6F2FF|AI Engine (Claude Haiku 3.5)|
:Wrap inputs in XML delimiters:\n<ocr_data>, <voice_transcript>,\n<firm_context>; <<#Orange>>
:Generate Personalised Draft Email\n(subject, HTML body, plain text); <<#Orange>>
:Validate response against Zod schema\n(retry on malformed output); <<#Orange>>

|#E6F2FF|API Gateway (Fastify) — Azure Container Apps|
:Store Lead PII & Draft in CosmosDB PostgreSQL\n(TDE via Key Vault, TLS 1.3 in transit,\nCitus tenant_id sharding + RLS isolation); <<#Orange>>
:Log lead capture event via audit-client\n→ signalcaptureai-audit-service\n(append-only, 7-year retention);

|#FFCCCC|Sales Rep|
:Human-in-the-Loop:\nReview & Approve Draft Email;

|#E6F2FF|Email Service (Graph API + ACS)|
:Sanitise CRLF in all dynamic fields;
:Inject tracking pixel (open detection);
:Dispatch Email via Microsoft 365 Graph API\n(from user's own mailbox, Mail.Send scope); <<#Red>>
note right
  OAuth tokens encrypted with
  Key Vault envelope encryption.
  Token rotation handled by
  email-oauth package.
end note

|#FFCCCC|Lead|
:Receives Personalised Follow-Up Email; <<#Red>>

|#E6F2FF|Email Service (Graph API + ACS)|
:Poll Inbox via Graph API (5min interval)\n→ Detect Reply Events;
:Record Open + Reply in email_tracking table;

|#E6F2FF|API Gateway (Fastify) — Azure Container Apps|
:Record Interaction Metrics\n(Scoped to Event / Tenant);
note right
  Automated retention purge:
  Solo/Starter/Growth — hard delete
  leads 90 days after capture.
  Enterprise — configurable retention
  (365 days default).
end note

if (GDPR Data Subject Request?) then (Query / Delete)
    |#E6F2FF|API Gateway — gdpr-tools|
    :Scan 7 PII tables for email/name match; <<#Orange>>
    :Cascade Delete\n(FK children before parents); <<#Orange>>
    :Generate Compliance Receipt\n(request ID, timestamp, affected tables,\nrow counts); <<#Orange>>
    :Log GDPR deletion via audit-client;
endif

stop
@enduml
